messages.content:
Give this to Claude to have him help you "paste" screenshots instead of having to drag them from files every time 

Paste screenshots directly into Claude Code (WSL)

If you want Claude to look at a screenshot, mockup, error message, etc. - just copy it to your
clipboard (Win+Shift+S, PrtSc, or right-click > Copy Image) and tell Claude:

"grab my clipboard"

That's it. Claude will pull the image from your Windows clipboard and view it.

How it works under the hood:
- Claude runs a PowerShell command that grabs the current image from your Windows clipboard
- Saves it to C:\Temp\clipboard_tmp.png
- Reads it with the Read tool (Claude can view images natively)

Setup (one time):

1. Make sure C:\Temp exists (create it if not)
2. Create a MEMORY.md file if you don't already have one. This is a new Claude Code feature - it's a
  persistent memory file that loads into every session's system prompt automatically, so Claude
remembers things across conversations without you having to repeat yourself.

2. Your memory file lives at:
~/.claude/projects/<your-project>/memory/MEMORY.md

2. Add this block to it:

## Clipboard Image Paste
When the user says "grab my clipboard", "paste my screenshot", or similar:
```bash
powershell.exe -NoProfile -Command "Add-Type -AssemblyName System.Windows.Forms; \$img =
[System.Windows.Forms.Clipboard]::GetImage(); if (\$img -eq \$null) { Write-Error 'No image'; exit 1
  }; \$img.Save('C:\Temp\clipboard_tmp.png', [System.Drawing.Imaging.ImageFormat]::Png); Write-Host
'OK'"
```
Then read `/mnt/c/Temp/clipboard_tmp.png` with the Read tool.

That's all. Every new session will know how to do it from now on. MEMORY.md is also a great place to
  put any other things you find yourself repeating to Claude - project conventions, common commands,
personal preferences, etc.
I'll be OOO tomorrow...will you make sure that we get detailed release notes to BPF?

ll done. Here's what Nathan needs:

 

  Branch: feature/worksuite-mcp-server on the wsapi repo

 

  What's there:
  - 12 source files (977 lines) for the full MCP server
  - WorkSuite.Mcp/SETUP_GUIDE.html - a styled HTML walkthrough covering:
    a. Prerequisites (.NET 9, Docker, Python, ngrok account)
    b. Getting the code (git checkout feature/worksuite-mcp-server)
    c. Starting Docker infrastructure (MongoDB + KurrentDB)
    d. Starting wsapi GraphQL API
    e. Generating a JWT token (Python one-liner with the dev signing key)
    f. Creating a tenant via GraphQL mutation
    g. Building & starting the MCP server with all env vars
    h. Installing & configuring ngrok
    i. Connecting Claude.ai (URL must end with /sse)
    j. Testing all 6 tools with example prompts
    - Plus troubleshooting section for common issues

 

  Nathan can open the HTML locally in a browser for a nice formatted guide, or just read it in his IDE. The guide is self-contained - no external
  dependencies.
